 2 mg daily) is approved and suggested by the manufacturer.

 This delivers 50% less pomalidomide to the patient, albeit at 100% of the price of full dosing.

 In summary, the establishment of the modified pomalidomide schedule would be an interesting option for our patients to achieve similar efficacy with fewer side effects.

